<subSubSection pageNumber="708" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="708">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="708">Note:</emphasis>
As pointed out by Harley (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="708">Watsonia</emphasis>
14: 86. 1982), Ietswaart (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="708">Leiden Bot. Ser.</emphasis>
4: 87. 1980) designated 743.12 (LINN) as the type of both 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Origanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="syriacum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="708">O. syriacum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="L. Harley" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1763" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Origanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="maru">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="708">O. maru</emphasis>
L. Harley
</taxonomicName>
stated &quot;while the sheet indicated is unquestionably the type of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1763" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Origanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="maru">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="708">O. maru</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, it can hardly be the type of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Origanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="syriacum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="708">O. syriacum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which apparently does not occur among the sheets in 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Linnaeus’">Linnaeus'</normalizedToken>
herbarium in London, and must be looked for elsewhere&quot;. Meikle (
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="708">Fl. Cyprus</emphasis>
2: 1267. 1985) stated &quot;TYPE: Probably the illustration in Lobel...t. 499 (1591)&quot;, i.e. the Plantin illustration, but his use of the word 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“probably”">&quot;probably&quot;</normalizedToken>
contradicts Art. 7.11 of the Code.
</paragraph>
